1
00:00:07,721 --> 00:00:09,481
[If you don't turn yourself in,
your limbs will rot and you'll die]

2
00:00:37,938 --> 00:00:40,918
[All characters and events are fictional,
and any resemblance is coincidental]

3
00:00:40,918 --> 00:00:43,238
[Scenes with children and animals were filmed
safely under professional supervision]

4
00:00:43,238 --> 00:00:44,905
[Central Veterans Hall]

5
00:00:44,905 --> 00:00:48,672
This recent redevelopment and reconstruction
reform bill has drawn strong reactions.

6
00:00:48,672 --> 00:00:52,572
There are many saying that
it's finally a bill that reflects reality.

7
00:00:52,572 --> 00:00:56,705
Association officials are also welcoming it,
saying negotiations have become much easier.

8
00:00:56,705 --> 00:00:59,238
How frustrated must they have been?

9
00:00:59,238 --> 00:01:01,438
The times are changing fast,

10
00:01:01,438 --> 00:01:03,838
but the law couldn't keep up with them.

11
00:01:03,838 --> 00:01:05,238
Even after the policy took effect,

12
00:01:05,238 --> 00:01:08,405
your approval ratings have stayed strong.

13
00:01:08,405 --> 00:01:11,605
At this rate, you might even want to start
thinking about a future presidential run.

14
00:01:11,605 --> 00:01:15,241
No, right now it's more about
public sentiment than the presidency.

15
00:01:16,041 --> 00:01:20,272
Is the interview we did
last time airing today?

16
00:01:20,272 --> 00:01:23,638
Yes, it'll be on air in 10 minutes.

17
00:01:23,638 --> 00:01:25,738
Let's watch it.

18
00:01:25,738 --> 00:01:28,713
<i>The prime suspect
in the Kangseng Serial Murder Case</i>

19
00:01:28,713 --> 00:01:30,705
<i>which once plunged
the entire nation into fear,</i>

20
00:01:30,705 --> 00:01:34,405
[Serial Murder Case: Suspect Identified]
<i>has been identified 33 years after the crime.</i>

21
00:01:34,405 --> 00:01:36,038
Wait.

22
00:01:36,038 --> 00:01:37,805
Switch back to that channel.

23
00:01:37,805 --> 00:01:39,938
Sure.

24
00:01:39,938 --> 00:01:42,105
<i>Police said at a briefing this morning that,</i>

25
00:01:42,105 --> 00:01:44,972
<i>following a re-examination
by the National Forensic Service,</i>

26
00:01:44,972 --> 00:01:48,338
<i>they are investigating
after being informed that</i>

27
00:01:48,338 --> 00:01:51,005
[Prime suspect: male inmate in his 60s]
<i>an inmate's DNA matches evidence</i>

28
00:01:51,005 --> 00:01:52,972
<i>from three crime scenes.</i>

29
00:01:52,972 --> 00:01:57,572
<i>The suspect is a man in his 60s,
Mr. Lee, currently incarcerated...</i>

30
00:02:08,205 --> 00:02:10,947
[Episode 5]

31
00:02:18,705 --> 00:02:21,972
Sun Young, can you hear me?

32
00:02:21,972 --> 00:02:23,105
Ji Won.

33
00:02:23,105 --> 00:02:24,738
Yeah.

34
00:02:27,872 --> 00:02:29,938
Why am I here?

35
00:02:31,038 --> 00:02:32,572
Don't you remember?

36
00:02:32,572 --> 00:02:35,572
What happened to you?

37
00:02:35,572 --> 00:02:37,205
Well...

38
00:02:49,272 --> 00:02:51,338
Someone was chasing me.

39
00:02:52,238 --> 00:02:54,538
<i>I tried to run away from that person...</i>

40
00:02:54,538 --> 00:02:56,338
<i>Who was it?</i>

41
00:02:57,672 --> 00:02:59,272
I don't know.

42
00:03:03,072 --> 00:03:04,105
Ki Beom...

43
00:03:04,105 --> 00:03:06,305
What happened to Ki Beom?

44
00:03:06,305 --> 00:03:08,205
We don't know yet.

45
00:03:10,205 --> 00:03:12,072
Sun Young, where are you going?

46
00:03:12,072 --> 00:03:14,238
I've got to find Ki Beom!

47
00:03:21,005 --> 00:03:24,072
Sun Young, you...

48
00:03:34,438 --> 00:03:36,338
<i>Is this that punk?</i>

49
00:03:36,338 --> 00:03:37,572
<i>I found the owner of the handkerchief.</i>

50
00:03:37,572 --> 00:03:39,038
<i>This is Sun Young's handkerchief?</i>

51
00:03:39,038 --> 00:03:41,072
<i>Sun Young made this herself.</i>

52
00:03:41,072 --> 00:03:44,105
<i>The only person who could have
something identical to this is Ki Beom.</i>

53
00:03:44,105 --> 00:03:46,405
<i>So he only covered his face in front of me?</i>

54
00:03:46,405 --> 00:03:48,005
<i>Why?</i>

55
00:04:07,817 --> 00:04:08,905
[Restricted Area]

56
00:04:08,905 --> 00:04:10,505
Sir!

57
00:04:11,705 --> 00:04:12,905
What happened?

58
00:04:12,905 --> 00:04:14,505
Well...

59
00:04:14,505 --> 00:04:16,041
We lost him.

60
00:04:17,609 --> 00:04:18,793
[Surgery in progress]

61
00:04:21,219 --> 00:04:22,438
Doctor,

62
00:04:22,438 --> 00:04:24,405
how is he?

63
00:04:24,405 --> 00:04:26,338
The surgery went well.

64
00:04:26,338 --> 00:04:29,605
Fortunately, there is no organ damage,
so he is in stable condition.

65
00:04:29,605 --> 00:04:33,638
Infection is the main concern,
but we'll monitor him for now.

66
00:04:35,172 --> 00:04:38,238
These are the patient's belongings.

67
00:04:41,838 --> 00:04:46,072
Prosecutor Cha went there to deliver this...

68
00:04:49,772 --> 00:04:53,172
[Police Officer ID: Kang Tae Joo]

69
00:04:59,372 --> 00:05:01,138
Did you not know you were pregnant?

70
00:05:01,138 --> 00:05:02,838
It seems like it's been about three months.

71
00:05:02,838 --> 00:05:06,638
- Pregnant?
- Oh dear, you didn't know.

72
00:05:07,472 --> 00:05:09,905
And the baby? Is the baby okay?

73
00:05:09,905 --> 00:05:12,772
Yes, there's nothing to worry about.

74
00:05:12,772 --> 00:05:16,105
Fortunately, there are
no signs of concussion.

75
00:05:16,105 --> 00:05:20,272
As long as the scrapes on your legs
are treated well, you should be fine.

76
00:05:20,272 --> 00:05:24,938
If you feel dizzy or develop headaches later,
make sure to get checked.

77
00:05:25,672 --> 00:05:27,505
- Okay.
- Thank you.

78
00:05:30,905 --> 00:05:32,838
Oh, Sun Young...

79
00:05:32,838 --> 00:05:35,872
Oh, Sun Young, Sun Young.

80
00:05:37,905 --> 00:05:40,638
Don't tell my brother, please.
I'll tell him myself later.

81
00:05:40,638 --> 00:05:42,238
Alright, alright.

82
00:05:44,005 --> 00:05:45,005
Kang Sun Young.

83
00:05:45,005 --> 00:05:47,072
Who is it? That punk?

84
00:05:47,072 --> 00:05:48,305
Tae Joo.

85
00:05:48,305 --> 00:05:50,238
Who's the culprit? I'm asking!

86
00:05:50,238 --> 00:05:51,938
You, hey!

87
00:05:53,472 --> 00:05:55,272
What are you doing
with someone who just woke up?

88
00:05:55,272 --> 00:05:56,772
Answer me!

89
00:05:56,772 --> 00:05:58,805
I don't know. I didn't see him.

90
00:05:58,805 --> 00:05:59,905
Are you sure?

91
00:05:59,905 --> 00:06:02,272
Why would I lie?

92
00:06:04,405 --> 00:06:06,538
You were with Ki Beom.

93
00:06:06,538 --> 00:06:09,238
Why are you bringing Ki Beom up?

94
00:06:09,238 --> 00:06:11,538
Are you seriously suspecting him?

95
00:06:15,305 --> 00:06:16,538
Are you out of your mind?

96
00:06:16,538 --> 00:06:18,138
Then what about all this?

97
00:06:18,138 --> 00:06:21,305
Where did Ki Beom go?
Why did this happen to you?

98
00:06:21,305 --> 00:06:24,972
I'll explain. Stop pushing me.

99
00:06:28,038 --> 00:06:31,872
So Ki Beom locked you
in a warehouse and left on his own?

100
00:06:33,105 --> 00:06:35,838
He said he would handle everything himself.

101
00:06:36,472 --> 00:06:38,205
I went after Ki Beom a bit late,

102
00:06:38,205 --> 00:06:40,938
and someone started following me,
so at first I thought it was the police.

103
00:06:40,938 --> 00:06:44,738
I thought they were tailing me to catch
Ki Beom, so I tried to shake them off.

104
00:06:44,738 --> 00:06:47,272
Then I fell into the ditch.

105
00:06:47,972 --> 00:06:49,438
That's all.

106
00:06:49,438 --> 00:06:51,972
I don't remember anything after that.

107
00:06:53,072 --> 00:06:54,672
Kang Sun Young.

108
00:06:55,305 --> 00:06:58,038
If you're lying just to protect Ki Beom...

109
00:06:58,038 --> 00:07:00,072
It's all true, Tae Joo.

110
00:07:01,372 --> 00:07:02,972
Are you sure?

111
00:07:07,972 --> 00:07:10,072
What happened to Ki Beom?

112
00:07:10,972 --> 00:07:12,905
We're still chasing him.

113
00:07:12,905 --> 00:07:14,305
Ki Beom was going to turn himself in.

114
00:07:14,305 --> 00:07:15,505
I stopped him.

115
00:07:15,505 --> 00:07:17,038
What?

116
00:07:17,038 --> 00:07:18,438
Hey, what were you thinking...

117
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:19,772
You should've told me.

118
00:07:19,772 --> 00:07:21,305
I was going to.

119
00:07:21,305 --> 00:07:23,305
But when I went to the police station,
you weren't there.

120
00:07:23,305 --> 00:07:25,038
And they said Jeon Kyeong Ho might die.

121
00:07:25,038 --> 00:07:26,538
- What am I supposed to do, then?
- Die? He won't die.

122
00:07:26,538 --> 00:07:28,205
That punk woke up.

123
00:07:28,205 --> 00:07:30,172
No need to worry.

124
00:07:31,472 --> 00:07:33,338
Oh, thank goodness.

125
00:07:35,638 --> 00:07:38,238
But he's not the problem right now.

126
00:07:38,238 --> 00:07:40,205
Then what is the problem?

127
00:07:49,955 --> 00:07:58,723
[Kangseng Jaeil Hospital]

128
00:08:08,572 --> 00:08:11,849
Don't worry about Sun Young.
I'll stay by her side.

129
00:08:13,305 --> 00:08:14,972
I'm counting on you.

130
00:08:16,772 --> 00:08:18,872
Isn't it strange?

131
00:08:18,872 --> 00:08:23,738
If Ki Beom were the culprit, he wouldn't
have locked Sun Young in the warehouse.

132
00:08:26,972 --> 00:08:28,172
Tae Joo.

133
00:08:28,172 --> 00:08:29,172
The Ki Beom we knew...

134
00:08:29,172 --> 00:08:30,772
Ji Won.

135
00:08:31,405 --> 00:08:34,205
I'm going to erase the Ki Beom I knew.

136
00:08:34,205 --> 00:08:36,405
That's better for him too.

137
00:08:38,105 --> 00:08:40,605
Whether he's the culprit or not...

138
00:09:07,872 --> 00:09:10,905
[Kangseng Jaeil Hospital
Nighttime Emergency Room]

139
00:09:17,238 --> 00:09:18,805
You know it, right?

140
00:09:18,805 --> 00:09:20,972
The reason why Ki Beom is on the run...

141
00:09:29,938 --> 00:09:33,838
Tell me, what exactly is going on?

142
00:09:39,738 --> 00:09:41,538
Ki Beom is...

143
00:09:43,305 --> 00:09:46,305
a suspect in the serial murder case.

144
00:09:47,738 --> 00:09:49,372
What?

145
00:10:02,672 --> 00:10:08,605
I thought you were my father's son.

146
00:10:08,605 --> 00:10:11,305
But I can't stand brothers.

147
00:10:11,305 --> 00:10:13,305
Friends are fine, though.

148
00:10:24,972 --> 00:10:28,638
Si Young!

149
00:10:28,638 --> 00:10:30,805
What on earth is going on?

150
00:10:30,805 --> 00:10:32,405
Si Young!

151
00:10:36,205 --> 00:10:37,805
It was you, wasn't it?

152
00:10:38,905 --> 00:10:40,838
You did this, right?

153
00:10:40,838 --> 00:10:43,338
You punk, you really did this to Si Young!

154
00:10:47,638 --> 00:10:49,705
If I hadn't been drinking...

155
00:10:49,705 --> 00:10:52,572
Call Cha Si Young's house, you punk.

156
00:10:53,238 --> 00:10:55,572
There's no one at his house.

157
00:10:59,472 --> 00:11:01,372
What do you mean no one?

158
00:11:03,438 --> 00:11:07,305
Si Young lives alone in that big house.

159
00:11:10,605 --> 00:11:11,705
What about his family?

160
00:11:11,705 --> 00:11:15,972
His parents and older brother
are probably in Seoul.

161
00:11:15,972 --> 00:11:19,205
Are you interrogating me right now?

162
00:11:23,038 --> 00:11:25,805
Call me when this punk wakes up.

163
00:11:27,105 --> 00:11:29,205
That punk...

164
00:11:40,538 --> 00:11:42,805
Does he not have a home phone number?

165
00:11:45,738 --> 00:11:49,772
[Cha Jun Young]

166
00:11:51,972 --> 00:11:56,305
Why would a superintendent
step in over a sergeant's resignation?

167
00:11:56,305 --> 00:11:57,305
A superintendent?

168
00:11:57,305 --> 00:11:59,205
You don't know Superintendent Cha Jun Young?

169
00:11:59,205 --> 00:12:02,338
The youngest ever
to become a superintendent in Korea.

170
00:12:03,338 --> 00:12:07,138
Cha Jun Young, Cha Si Young...

171
00:12:08,099 --> 00:12:13,827
[Payphone Booth]

172
00:12:23,305 --> 00:12:24,472
Hello?

173
00:12:24,472 --> 00:12:27,372
<i>Hello, is this Superintendent Cha Jun Young?</i>

174
00:12:27,372 --> 00:12:28,805
Speaking.

175
00:12:28,805 --> 00:12:32,005
<i>This is Sergeant Kang Tae Joo
from Kangseng Station.</i>

176
00:12:32,005 --> 00:12:33,405
Sergeant?

177
00:12:33,405 --> 00:12:36,638
Why would a sergeant call me?

178
00:12:36,638 --> 00:12:38,872
And at this hour?

179
00:12:38,872 --> 00:12:41,105
<i>I'm calling about Prosecutor Cha Si Young.</i>

180
00:12:41,105 --> 00:12:44,572
Prosecutor Cha Si Young
is currently in the hospital.

181
00:12:44,572 --> 00:12:45,938
Why is he in the hospital?

182
00:12:45,938 --> 00:12:49,505
He was stabbed during the arrest
of a serial killer suspect.

183
00:12:49,505 --> 00:12:50,761
Jeez...

184
00:12:54,138 --> 00:12:56,638
<i>Wait, did he catch the suspect then?</i>

185
00:12:56,638 --> 00:12:57,638
No.

186
00:12:57,638 --> 00:12:59,305
Are you sure that's the culprit?

187
00:12:59,305 --> 00:13:03,405
<i>It's too early to say for certain.</i>

188
00:13:04,572 --> 00:13:06,272
Yeah?

189
00:13:06,905 --> 00:13:09,972
The surgery went well.
I thought you might want to know.

190
00:13:09,972 --> 00:13:11,705
I'll hang up now.

191
00:13:11,705 --> 00:13:14,105
<i>Wait, how did you know I'm his brother?</i>

192
00:13:14,105 --> 00:13:16,805
Did he go around bragging about it?

193
00:13:16,805 --> 00:13:18,605
<i>I figured it out from the contacts.</i>

194
00:13:18,605 --> 00:13:19,905
Figured it out?

195
00:13:19,905 --> 00:13:24,572
Cha Jun Young, Cha Si Young...
they're obviously sibling names.

196
00:13:24,572 --> 00:13:26,572
Okay, then I'll hang up now.

197
00:13:29,838 --> 00:13:32,972
What's with this guy?
He's only asking about the suspect...

198
00:13:32,972 --> 00:13:35,472
His own brother got stabbed.

199
00:13:36,538 --> 00:13:40,272
So he lost the suspect?

200
00:13:49,538 --> 00:13:52,438
Hey, Kang Shik, it's Ki Hwan.

201
00:13:52,438 --> 00:13:54,872
Do you know where Ki Beom is?

202
00:13:55,572 --> 00:13:57,205
You don't know?

203
00:13:57,938 --> 00:14:00,572
If you somehow get in touch
with Ki Beom or anything,

204
00:14:00,572 --> 00:14:03,638
could you please tell him to contact me?

205
00:14:03,638 --> 00:14:05,038
- Well, no, I mean...
- Oh, dear.

206
00:14:05,038 --> 00:14:07,172
Alright, I'm hanging up.

207
00:14:08,438 --> 00:14:11,372
Who is calling so early? Is it Ki Beom?

208
00:14:11,372 --> 00:14:12,905
Oh, Ki Beom... yes, it's Ki Beom.

209
00:14:12,905 --> 00:14:15,872
He just called to say he arrived safely
at his friend's house.

210
00:14:15,872 --> 00:14:16,938
Oh, dear.

211
00:14:16,938 --> 00:14:19,038
Did Ki Beom go somewhere?

212
00:14:21,205 --> 00:14:22,805
Where was it again?

213
00:14:22,805 --> 00:14:24,705
Did he say Haenam?

214
00:14:24,705 --> 00:14:28,105
He once went to help out with farm work
at a friend's place there.

215
00:14:28,105 --> 00:14:30,605
Tae Joo, what brings you here so early?

216
00:14:30,605 --> 00:14:33,638
I was grocery shopping
and ran into him nearby.

217
00:14:33,638 --> 00:14:34,638
Thank you.

218
00:14:34,638 --> 00:14:36,272
Thanks to you, Tae Joo,
we got home without any trouble.

219
00:14:36,272 --> 00:14:38,205
Don't mention it.
I don't get to visit often anyway.

220
00:14:38,205 --> 00:14:41,238
- Ma'am, everything okay?
- Hey,

221
00:14:41,238 --> 00:14:42,705
something good happened to you?

222
00:14:42,705 --> 00:14:43,805
What good would there be?

223
00:14:43,805 --> 00:14:45,838
Hey, did something good happen?

224
00:14:52,338 --> 00:14:54,638
Did Ki Beom get caught?
Is that why you are here?

225
00:14:54,638 --> 00:14:57,105
No, it's nothing like that.

226
00:14:59,572 --> 00:15:02,705
Don't you dare mention Ki Beom to my mother.

227
00:15:02,705 --> 00:15:05,405
I just said he went to visit a friend
in the countryside.

228
00:15:05,405 --> 00:15:07,638
So you don't know where Ki Beom is, either?

229
00:15:07,638 --> 00:15:09,772
Don't know. That punk...

230
00:15:09,772 --> 00:15:12,338
I haven't heard from him
since that incident yesterday.

231
00:15:13,805 --> 00:15:15,638
Is that guy okay?

232
00:15:15,638 --> 00:15:17,005
Jeon Kyeong Ho?

233
00:15:17,005 --> 00:15:18,938
Don't worry about that punk.

234
00:15:18,938 --> 00:15:20,272
It'll be settled with an agreement.

235
00:15:20,272 --> 00:15:22,005
What? Are you sure?

236
00:15:22,005 --> 00:15:24,438
He's done plenty of wrong himself too.

237
00:15:24,438 --> 00:15:28,038
Anyway, we need Ki Beom
for the settlement paperwork.

238
00:15:28,038 --> 00:15:29,205
If you find him, send him to me immediately.

239
00:15:29,205 --> 00:15:33,038
Okay, oh... thank you so much, Tae Joo.

240
00:15:33,038 --> 00:15:34,972
Thank you, really.

241
00:15:34,972 --> 00:15:36,872
- I'm leaving.
- Alright.

242
00:15:36,872 --> 00:15:39,363
- Take care on your way.
- Yeah.

243
00:15:41,672 --> 00:15:42,872
[Period for Reporting and Surrendering Spies]
He's not home?

244
00:15:42,872 --> 00:15:45,572
Then, is there anywhere else he might go?

245
00:15:45,572 --> 00:15:48,238
Even his family didn't seem to know
Ki Beom's whereabouts.

246
00:15:48,238 --> 00:15:51,838
How do you know they weren't just pretending?

247
00:15:51,838 --> 00:15:55,172
His family thinks Ki Beom
is running from assault charges.

248
00:15:55,172 --> 00:15:58,172
His mother doesn't even
seem to know that much.

249
00:16:00,305 --> 00:16:02,772
Since news of Jeon Kyeong Ho
dropping the charges was leaked,

250
00:16:02,772 --> 00:16:06,038
if Ki Beom isn't the serial killer,

251
00:16:06,038 --> 00:16:07,738
he'll respond to that.

252
00:16:07,738 --> 00:16:11,505
So are you saying Ki Beom
might not be the culprit?

253
00:16:11,505 --> 00:16:13,272
What nonsense are you talking about now?

254
00:16:13,272 --> 00:16:14,705
If it's not Ki Beom, then who is it?

255
00:16:14,705 --> 00:16:18,905
At the place they went to find Ki Beom,
Detective Kang's sister almost got hurt.

256
00:16:18,905 --> 00:16:21,072
And the prosecutor was stabbed.

257
00:16:21,072 --> 00:16:22,405
It can't be anyone else.

258
00:16:22,405 --> 00:16:24,472
Right now, it's still
just circumstantial evidence.

259
00:16:24,472 --> 00:16:26,838
The circumstantial evidence is piling up!

260
00:16:29,138 --> 00:16:32,505
Sir, we should put Lee Ki Beom
on the wanted list now,

261
00:16:32,505 --> 00:16:34,805
and search his house and the bookstore.

262
00:16:35,472 --> 00:16:38,638
Prosecutor Cha Si Young
might have seen the suspect.

263
00:16:38,638 --> 00:16:42,305
What if the person Prosecutor Cha saw
wasn't Lee Ki Beom?

264
00:16:42,305 --> 00:16:44,538
I'm telling you, there's no way that's true.

265
00:16:44,538 --> 00:16:48,105
Let's just wait until
Prosecutor Cha wakes up, okay?

266
00:16:48,105 --> 00:16:49,472
- Sir.
- Sir.

267
00:16:49,472 --> 00:16:50,605
Prosecutor Cha will wake up soon.

268
00:16:50,605 --> 00:16:52,805
Right now, every second matters.

269
00:16:52,805 --> 00:16:53,872
Right, sir.

270
00:16:53,872 --> 00:16:55,972
We really don't have time.

271
00:16:55,972 --> 00:16:57,672
- Sir.
- Darn it, you're too loud.

272
00:16:57,672 --> 00:17:00,138
Just be quiet for a second, and let me think.

273
00:17:00,138 --> 00:17:02,338
Okay? We don't have time, sir!

274
00:17:02,338 --> 00:17:04,005
Oh, jeez!

275
00:17:06,905 --> 00:17:09,005
Yes, this is Kangseng Police Station.

276
00:17:10,038 --> 00:17:11,593
What?

277
00:17:11,593 --> 00:17:13,472
A murder case?

278
00:17:18,705 --> 00:17:21,638
Joo Hee, wake up!

279
00:17:22,405 --> 00:17:24,905
Time to eat.

280
00:17:25,872 --> 00:17:28,638
Why are you suddenly sleeping in?

281
00:17:28,638 --> 00:17:32,505
Get up and eat. You have to go to school.

282
00:17:38,805 --> 00:17:40,872
Her mother found her in the morning.

283
00:17:40,872 --> 00:17:42,905
There are signs of strangulation.

284
00:17:42,905 --> 00:17:46,405
Gosh. She's way too young.

285
00:17:55,972 --> 00:17:57,545
The pattern is different.

286
00:17:57,545 --> 00:17:59,038
[No entry, under investigation]
Was the front gate open?

287
00:17:59,038 --> 00:18:00,972
They said it was open
when they checked it this morning.

288
00:18:00,972 --> 00:18:02,538
Was she alone yesterday?

289
00:18:02,538 --> 00:18:05,572
No. Her parents were sleeping
in the next room.

290
00:18:05,572 --> 00:18:08,305
Wow, that guy is a total scumbag.

291
00:18:08,305 --> 00:18:11,372
Her parents were right there,
but still he did that to the girl...

292
00:18:11,372 --> 00:18:12,777
Under one roof...

293
00:18:12,777 --> 00:18:15,721
He's completely out of his mind.

294
00:18:18,722 --> 00:18:20,105
My gosh.

295
00:18:20,105 --> 00:18:22,115
- What is it?
- Move.

296
00:18:26,672 --> 00:18:27,972
What happened?

297
00:18:27,972 --> 00:18:29,305
They say a child got killed.

298
00:18:29,305 --> 00:18:30,472
- What happened?
- Is it true?

299
00:18:30,472 --> 00:18:31,872
- A middle schooler was found dead at home.
- Why?

300
00:18:31,872 --> 00:18:34,072
Don't tell me it's a serial case?

301
00:18:38,438 --> 00:18:40,572
What?

302
00:18:40,572 --> 00:18:43,038
Right? The place from yesterday?

303
00:18:55,538 --> 00:18:57,372
Got you!

304
00:18:58,205 --> 00:18:59,689
You little rat.

305
00:19:02,072 --> 00:19:03,538
Hey, Do Hyeong Gu!

306
00:19:03,538 --> 00:19:07,072
In 13 years on the job,
that was your best moment!

307
00:19:07,072 --> 00:19:08,838
- Did you see that?
- That was cool.

308
00:19:08,838 --> 00:19:11,738
- We caught him together, okay?
- I've got to pee. I'll be right back.

309
00:19:11,738 --> 00:19:12,772
Hurry up and come back.

310
00:19:12,772 --> 00:19:14,138
Ah, that punk...

311
00:19:14,138 --> 00:19:19,472
What is he, a puppy? He just goes around
marking his territory everywhere.

312
00:19:20,472 --> 00:19:24,572
Go farther away to piss, you punk.

313
00:19:24,572 --> 00:19:26,405
Hey, where are you going?

314
00:19:26,405 --> 00:19:27,805
Hey! Get him!

315
00:19:27,805 --> 00:19:29,923
Hey, cut it out, you punk!

316
00:19:29,923 --> 00:19:31,740
That punk!

317
00:19:35,672 --> 00:19:37,538
Darn it, you punk!

318
00:19:37,538 --> 00:19:41,638
If this was Lee Ki Beom's doing, shouldn't we
say something now? About yesterday.

319
00:19:41,638 --> 00:19:44,338
Jeez, this is driving me crazy.

320
00:19:44,338 --> 00:19:46,883
How does this even make sense?

321
00:19:50,772 --> 00:19:52,329
Hey!

322
00:19:52,329 --> 00:19:53,638
Oh my.

323
00:19:53,638 --> 00:19:56,272
Hey!

324
00:19:56,272 --> 00:19:58,105
What is all this nonsense?

325
00:19:58,105 --> 00:20:00,138
Why did our Joo Hee die?

326
00:20:00,138 --> 00:20:04,005
I didn't hear a thing while I was sleeping.

327
00:20:04,005 --> 00:20:06,472
I'm her father,

328
00:20:06,472 --> 00:20:11,338
but I didn't even notice
my own child dying right next to me.

329
00:20:11,338 --> 00:20:16,272
I was... I was sleeping just next door!

330
00:20:16,272 --> 00:20:18,905
Gosh... what kind of father am I?

331
00:20:18,905 --> 00:20:21,138
Wait...

332
00:20:21,138 --> 00:20:23,472
What are we going to do about poor Joo Hee?

333
00:20:23,472 --> 00:20:25,705
How can this happen to her?

334
00:20:25,705 --> 00:20:27,605
It's all my fault!

335
00:20:27,605 --> 00:20:30,272
I killed her! I killed her!

336
00:20:30,272 --> 00:20:32,672
Why would it be your fault?

337
00:20:32,672 --> 00:20:36,138
It's the darn cops' fault
for not catching a single murderer.

338
00:20:36,138 --> 00:20:37,205
That's right!

339
00:20:37,205 --> 00:20:38,438
How many times has this happened now?

340
00:20:38,438 --> 00:20:39,705
Is this even a place where people can live?

341
00:20:39,705 --> 00:20:43,805
We can be careful outside at night,
but what if we're killed in our own beds?

342
00:20:43,805 --> 00:20:44,938
Exactly.

343
00:20:44,938 --> 00:20:48,038
People are getting murdered day after day.

344
00:20:48,038 --> 00:20:50,605
How can anyone live like this?

345
00:20:50,605 --> 00:20:52,238
Exactly!

346
00:20:53,443 --> 00:20:55,805
- Sir!
- Come on!

347
00:20:55,805 --> 00:20:57,638
Why are you doing this?

348
00:21:00,138 --> 00:21:02,305
Wait, hold on.

349
00:21:02,305 --> 00:21:03,972
- Wait, just a moment please.
- Sir.

350
00:21:03,972 --> 00:21:07,105
- Please calm down. It's okay, calm down.
- Sir...

351
00:21:07,105 --> 00:21:09,038
I'm the one in charge.

352
00:21:09,038 --> 00:21:12,405
The lack of progress
in the investigation so far...

353
00:21:12,405 --> 00:21:14,172
Yes, I have no excuse.

354
00:21:14,172 --> 00:21:16,572
As the chief, I bear
the greatest responsibility.

355
00:21:16,572 --> 00:21:18,705
But our detectives

356
00:21:18,705 --> 00:21:21,572
and officers are all doing their best

357
00:21:21,572 --> 00:21:24,172
day and night in their respective roles.

358
00:21:24,172 --> 00:21:27,872
So if you could just trust us

359
00:21:27,872 --> 00:21:30,938
a little longer and wait, we will...

360
00:21:30,938 --> 00:21:32,972
Wait for what?

361
00:21:32,972 --> 00:21:34,238
Let's just leave.

362
00:21:34,238 --> 00:21:35,572
Please stop this.

363
00:21:35,572 --> 00:21:36,672
We will...

364
00:21:36,672 --> 00:21:40,705
- We will definitely catch the culprit.
- When?

365
00:21:43,438 --> 00:21:45,038
- What are you doing?
- Do it properly.

366
00:22:22,672 --> 00:22:27,238
[Kangseng Police Station]

367
00:22:29,638 --> 00:22:31,338
- Hurry up!
- What is it?

368
00:22:31,338 --> 00:22:32,472
Jeez.

369
00:22:32,472 --> 00:22:34,638
What's with this mess?

370
00:22:34,638 --> 00:22:35,938
What's going on?

371
00:22:35,938 --> 00:22:37,638
The superintendent's coming. Line up quickly!

372
00:22:37,638 --> 00:22:39,638
The superintendent's here!

373
00:22:39,638 --> 00:22:41,305
Superintendent!

374
00:22:41,305 --> 00:22:43,538
Put this on first.

375
00:22:44,972 --> 00:22:47,338
Dae Ho, take that!

376
00:22:49,005 --> 00:22:50,205
Okay, he's coming.

377
00:22:50,205 --> 00:22:51,205
One moment, please.

378
00:22:51,205 --> 00:22:53,438
- The superintendent?
- Everyone, line up!

379
00:23:02,505 --> 00:23:04,205
Everyone, attention!

380
00:23:06,338 --> 00:23:07,972
Salute!

381
00:23:13,405 --> 00:23:15,305
Welcome, sir.

382
00:23:25,605 --> 00:23:26,738
Why is he here?

383
00:23:26,738 --> 00:23:27,772
I don't know, either.

384
00:23:27,772 --> 00:23:29,905
Should we go in too?

385
00:23:35,805 --> 00:23:40,938
Even His Excellency
made this decision with great difficulty.

386
00:23:40,938 --> 00:23:44,072
He acknowledges all your hard work.

387
00:23:44,905 --> 00:23:48,405
Don't take this assignment as a demotion.

388
00:23:48,405 --> 00:23:53,938
Think of it as a chance to rest.

389
00:23:59,738 --> 00:24:02,672
Oh, this tea isn't bad.

390
00:24:31,772 --> 00:24:33,472
Give me some water.

391
00:24:34,805 --> 00:24:37,538
Si Young, are you awake?

392
00:24:38,272 --> 00:24:39,372
I said water.

393
00:24:39,372 --> 00:24:40,672
Water, water...

394
00:24:40,672 --> 00:24:43,405
Excuse me! Doctor!

395
00:24:50,938 --> 00:24:52,872
The wound has healed well.

396
00:24:52,872 --> 00:24:55,672
But avoid getting it wet
when bathing for now.

397
00:24:55,672 --> 00:24:57,072
So can I be discharged?

398
00:24:57,072 --> 00:24:59,738
Let's decide after checking tomorrow.

399
00:24:59,738 --> 00:25:01,372
Alright, then...

400
00:25:05,038 --> 00:25:06,672
Thank you!

401
00:25:10,372 --> 00:25:12,605
You're incredibly lucky it wasn't worse.

402
00:25:12,605 --> 00:25:15,872
You wouldn't wake up for so long,
so I thought you were in serious trouble.

403
00:25:15,872 --> 00:25:17,472
What about the culprit?

404
00:25:18,305 --> 00:25:20,105
Not caught yet.

405
00:25:21,072 --> 00:25:25,038
More importantly, the whole Kangseng
went crazy while you were asleep.

406
00:25:25,872 --> 00:25:30,205
<i>The National Police Agency holds Kangseng
Police accountable for the serial killings</i>

407
00:25:30,205 --> 00:25:35,038
<i>and demotes Park Eun Kyu
to the Jeolla Provincial Police Headquarters.</i>

408
00:25:35,038 --> 00:25:38,538
Wow, they replaced the police chief
in the middle of this?

409
00:25:38,538 --> 00:25:41,005
Even three team leaders? What's happening?

410
00:25:41,005 --> 00:25:45,572
<i>Superintendent Cha Jun Young,
the youngest in the country,</i>

411
00:25:45,572 --> 00:25:48,772
<i>has been appointed as the new chief
of Kangseng Police Station.</i>

412
00:25:49,838 --> 00:25:51,805
[Cha Jun Young]
<i>Public trust in law enforcement</i>

413
00:25:51,805 --> 00:25:56,172
<i>has hit rock bottom
due to the sluggish investigation so far.</i>

414
00:25:56,172 --> 00:25:57,772
We plan to deploy

415
00:25:57,772 --> 00:26:02,705
large-scale manpower and set up
a new investigation task force.

416
00:26:02,705 --> 00:26:04,972
You said you'd expedite the investigation.

417
00:26:04,972 --> 00:26:08,738
When can we expect visible results?

418
00:26:08,738 --> 00:26:11,738
It's difficult to give a specific timeframe,

419
00:26:11,738 --> 00:26:15,638
but if we move away from a passive approach
and act more aggressively,

420
00:26:15,638 --> 00:26:20,272
<i>I believe we can restore
our damaged reputation.</i>

421
00:26:20,272 --> 00:26:23,805
<i>Are you saying you're confident
you can restore trust</i>

422
00:26:23,805 --> 00:26:26,372
<i>from the victims and their families?</i>

423
00:26:26,372 --> 00:26:27,372
<i>On the honor of the police...</i>

424
00:26:27,372 --> 00:26:31,572
Wow, looks like some big shot's here.

425
00:26:31,572 --> 00:26:34,238
He's just a cop though.

426
00:26:37,072 --> 00:26:39,753
Good work.

427
00:26:41,505 --> 00:26:44,005
Don't feel so down.

428
00:26:44,005 --> 00:26:48,905
This horrific case is happening in the place
where you were born and raised.

429
00:26:48,905 --> 00:26:53,972
You must catch him on the honor
of Kangseng Police, no matter what.

430
00:26:53,972 --> 00:26:55,672
Yes, sir.

431
00:27:00,038 --> 00:27:01,672
Sir.

432
00:27:05,538 --> 00:27:07,572
Drive safely.

433
00:27:08,938 --> 00:27:11,038
- I'm leaving.
- Okay.

434
00:27:12,438 --> 00:27:14,238
Everyone, attention!

435
00:27:14,238 --> 00:27:16,872
Salute to Mr. Kim!

436
00:27:16,872 --> 00:27:18,772
Thank you for your hard work!

437
00:27:25,138 --> 00:27:26,772
Let's head inside.

438
00:27:28,505 --> 00:27:31,138
Where on earth is that punk Kang Tae Joo?

439
00:27:31,138 --> 00:27:33,872
He doesn't even know what Mr. Kim
did for him. What an ungrateful punk.

440
00:27:33,872 --> 00:27:35,605
Where did he go?

441
00:27:52,505 --> 00:27:54,838
Hey, what are you doing here?

442
00:27:55,472 --> 00:27:57,238
Were you waiting for me?

443
00:27:58,205 --> 00:28:00,172
Why are you grinning like that?

444
00:28:00,172 --> 00:28:01,938
You like getting transferred that much?

445
00:28:01,938 --> 00:28:03,977
If I'm being demoted to the seaside,
how could I not be happy?

446
00:28:03,977 --> 00:28:06,838
You know how much I love sea fishing.

447
00:28:09,005 --> 00:28:10,838
Take this.

448
00:28:10,838 --> 00:28:12,438
What's this?

449
00:28:16,538 --> 00:28:20,205
This still reeks of eggs.
Why do you keep wearing it?

450
00:28:20,205 --> 00:28:22,572
It bothers me.

451
00:28:22,572 --> 00:28:25,417
- Does it smell?
- Obviously! You think it doesn't?

452
00:28:28,838 --> 00:28:30,972
Since when do you have money?

453
00:28:30,972 --> 00:28:32,938
Just...

454
00:28:32,938 --> 00:28:34,605
I made quite a bit.

455
00:28:37,872 --> 00:28:39,372
But isn't it a bit oversized?

456
00:28:39,372 --> 00:28:42,038
Come on, you should be wearing that size.

457
00:28:42,705 --> 00:28:44,605
That way it covers your belly too.

458
00:28:44,605 --> 00:28:46,905
You're not even that skinny anyway.

459
00:28:46,905 --> 00:28:49,272
I don't have a belly, you punk!

460
00:28:51,372 --> 00:28:52,972
Tae Joo,

461
00:28:53,738 --> 00:28:55,438
you're a good detective.

462
00:28:55,438 --> 00:28:57,305
However,

463
00:28:57,305 --> 00:29:01,372
don't try to handle everything alone.
Work with your colleagues.

464
00:29:01,372 --> 00:29:03,972
From my experience,

465
00:29:03,972 --> 00:29:06,305
your colleagues are your greatest asset.

466
00:29:09,772 --> 00:29:11,738
Remember that, you punk.

467
00:29:19,338 --> 00:29:21,538
Thanks. I'm off.

468
00:29:44,805 --> 00:29:47,172
Nagging till the very end.

469
00:29:48,772 --> 00:29:51,338
Take care, sir.

470
00:29:54,638 --> 00:29:56,272
Autopsy results show

471
00:29:57,872 --> 00:30:01,472
the victim was sexually assaulted
and then strangled to death.

472
00:30:02,472 --> 00:30:03,772
Any clues on the culprit?

473
00:30:03,772 --> 00:30:08,505
Yes, what appears to be the suspect's hair
and bodily fluids were found at the scene.

474
00:30:08,505 --> 00:30:12,372
Once again, the suspect is identified
as a male with blood type B.

475
00:30:12,372 --> 00:30:13,972
That's it?

476
00:30:14,605 --> 00:30:16,405
Yes.

477
00:30:16,405 --> 00:30:18,205
There's nothing new at all!

478
00:30:18,205 --> 00:30:21,005
This is why people in charge get fired.

479
00:30:21,005 --> 00:30:22,605
- Sorry, sir.
- Jeez.

480
00:30:23,438 --> 00:30:25,338
Kang Tae Joo!

481
00:30:25,338 --> 00:30:27,405
- Yes, sir.
- What do you think?

482
00:30:27,405 --> 00:30:29,538
Is this also a serial murder case?

483
00:30:32,938 --> 00:30:36,005
I don't think it's a serial murder.

484
00:30:36,005 --> 00:30:37,472
Why?

485
00:30:37,472 --> 00:30:42,505
Unlike previous cases, this one involved
a home invasion, not an open-area attack.

486
00:30:42,505 --> 00:30:44,338
The victim was 14,

487
00:30:44,338 --> 00:30:47,472
which is different
from the previous age range.

488
00:30:47,472 --> 00:30:51,205
There's also no sign of the serial killer's

489
00:30:51,205 --> 00:30:53,305
usual binding pattern.

490
00:30:53,305 --> 00:30:54,938
Is that so?

491
00:30:59,638 --> 00:31:01,605
Are you okay?

492
00:31:01,605 --> 00:31:03,638
What's wrong with him now?
Do you need to take a dump?

493
00:31:03,638 --> 00:31:05,172
Pardon?

494
00:31:05,172 --> 00:31:06,872
Or do you have something to say?

495
00:31:07,572 --> 00:31:10,072
No, I mean, it's just that...

496
00:31:10,072 --> 00:31:12,838
Around 11 PM on the night of the crime,

497
00:31:12,838 --> 00:31:16,738
suspect Lee Ki Beom was spotted
near victim Lee Joo Hee's residence.

498
00:31:16,738 --> 00:31:19,738
He was probably running away
after committing the crime.

499
00:31:19,738 --> 00:31:21,338
This case...

500
00:31:22,105 --> 00:31:24,238
is clearly a serial murder.

501
00:31:24,238 --> 00:31:25,872
Yes.

502
00:31:26,772 --> 00:31:28,372
That's all from me.

503
00:31:32,872 --> 00:31:35,772
These guys are unbelievable.

504
00:31:36,405 --> 00:31:38,038
Huh?

505
00:31:39,005 --> 00:31:41,138
You hid something that important?

506
00:31:41,138 --> 00:31:42,985
Have you lost your mind?

507
00:31:43,772 --> 00:31:46,638
Fine, I admit I messed up.

508
00:31:46,638 --> 00:31:48,172
But how could I have known?

509
00:31:48,172 --> 00:31:51,138
That he'd kill again while fleeing?

510
00:31:51,785 --> 00:31:53,159
Darn it!

511
00:31:54,633 --> 00:31:59,205
Around 11 PM, that's right after
the attack on Prosecutor Cha.

512
00:31:59,205 --> 00:32:00,772
Right.

513
00:32:00,772 --> 00:32:03,038
So he escaped the scene
and hid in Lee Joo Hee's house.

514
00:32:03,038 --> 00:32:05,705
The alibi checks out perfectly,
and the timeline fits as well.

515
00:32:05,705 --> 00:32:07,905
Kang Tae Joo!

516
00:32:07,905 --> 00:32:10,105
Even now, you still think
Lee Ki Beom isn't the real killer?

517
00:32:10,105 --> 00:32:11,738
Even with this?

518
00:32:18,938 --> 00:32:21,205
His Excellency sent me.

519
00:32:21,205 --> 00:32:23,305
It's also Father's will.

520
00:32:24,005 --> 00:32:25,905
Father did?

521
00:32:25,905 --> 00:32:30,205
Whether it's democratization or what,
the aftermath of last June's protests still...

522
00:32:30,205 --> 00:32:34,172
Now, it's even about to
influence the upcoming by-election.

523
00:32:34,172 --> 00:32:35,572
But you know

524
00:32:35,572 --> 00:32:39,738
how crucial this election is for Father.

525
00:32:42,305 --> 00:32:46,505
So Father wants us brothers to take the lead

526
00:32:46,505 --> 00:32:49,705
and solve this case together.

527
00:32:49,705 --> 00:32:50,738
"Us brothers"?

528
00:32:50,738 --> 00:32:52,705
Yes.

529
00:32:52,705 --> 00:32:56,472
Does that mean you're accepting me
as your brother?

530
00:32:56,472 --> 00:33:00,338
Hey, have we ever not been brothers? Huh?

531
00:33:00,338 --> 00:33:02,672
We share the same father's blood.

532
00:33:02,672 --> 00:33:05,272
Now I'm starting to feel hurt.

533
00:33:19,505 --> 00:33:22,572
Get up, get up!

534
00:33:23,913 --> 00:33:25,321
You little punk.

535
00:33:28,872 --> 00:33:31,672
He'll do better next time.

536
00:33:31,672 --> 00:33:36,105
You know how smart Si Young is.

537
00:33:36,105 --> 00:33:37,872
Right?

538
00:33:37,872 --> 00:33:39,505
Si Young...

539
00:33:42,605 --> 00:33:44,505
Father, I was wrong.

540
00:33:44,505 --> 00:33:46,238
Please, just one more chance.

541
00:33:46,972 --> 00:33:49,172
Give me just one more chance, please.

542
00:33:49,172 --> 00:33:50,772
Please, just once.

543
00:33:55,772 --> 00:34:00,738
To live as my son in this house,
you must prove worthy.

544
00:34:00,738 --> 00:34:02,538
Remember that.

545
00:34:07,638 --> 00:34:12,405
[Cha Si Young: 2nd Place]

546
00:34:18,538 --> 00:34:20,672
Don't take Father's words lightly.

547
00:34:20,672 --> 00:34:22,838
You'll be out otherwise.

548
00:34:25,938 --> 00:34:30,405
You don't think you're
the only illegitimate child, do you?

549
00:34:33,001 --> 00:34:34,633
Jeez.

550
00:34:40,305 --> 00:34:43,805
Anyway, take care of yourself.

551
00:34:43,805 --> 00:34:45,772
Let's do our best.

552
00:34:45,772 --> 00:34:47,638
I'm leaving.

553
00:34:47,638 --> 00:34:49,238
Take care.

554
00:34:58,605 --> 00:35:00,405
"Us brothers"?

555
00:35:03,472 --> 00:35:07,438
There was a time I desperately
wanted to hear that.

556
00:35:09,172 --> 00:35:11,538
But now?

557
00:35:11,538 --> 00:35:14,972
I'm already too old
to play the spoiled little brother with you.

558
00:35:31,872 --> 00:35:33,572
Sir!

559
00:35:39,205 --> 00:35:41,738
I heard a new task force is being formed.

560
00:35:41,738 --> 00:35:44,905
Has the new team leader been decided?

561
00:35:47,538 --> 00:35:50,472
Why would that interest you?

562
00:35:50,472 --> 00:35:52,672
What, trying to get yourself in line early?

563
00:35:52,672 --> 00:35:54,938
I have zero interest in that.

564
00:35:56,072 --> 00:36:00,938
Isn't that a position
meant to stand up for subordinates,

565
00:36:00,938 --> 00:36:03,172
even if it means taking the blame?

566
00:36:03,172 --> 00:36:07,638
Please use your influence
to bring in someone like that.

567
00:36:23,372 --> 00:36:25,838
That little punk...

568
00:36:31,689 --> 00:36:34,052
Wow!

569
00:36:39,072 --> 00:36:41,205
Hey, what did you say?

570
00:36:41,205 --> 00:36:42,872
- Hey...
- What did you say

571
00:36:42,872 --> 00:36:44,838
to make him so pissed?

572
00:36:45,472 --> 00:36:46,972
Tell me.

573
00:36:46,972 --> 00:36:48,905
So I can use it too later.

574
00:36:48,905 --> 00:36:50,738
- Did you see it?
- Yeah, obviously.

575
00:36:50,738 --> 00:36:53,238
His face completely crumpled
after you said that.

576
00:36:53,238 --> 00:36:54,938
No, the culprit!

577
00:36:54,938 --> 00:36:57,938
- Did you see him or not?
- Ah, it hurts.

578
00:36:57,938 --> 00:37:00,405
I'm still a patient.

579
00:37:02,172 --> 00:37:04,272
I got stabbed, remember?

580
00:37:05,305 --> 00:37:07,938
Did you see him or not?

581
00:37:07,938 --> 00:37:09,838
I didn't.

582
00:37:14,605 --> 00:37:16,038
What?

583
00:37:16,038 --> 00:37:20,772
Were you expecting some other name from me?

584
00:37:20,772 --> 00:37:22,872
Are you still not convinced?

585
00:37:22,872 --> 00:37:24,938
That Lee Ki Beom is the killer?

586
00:37:28,472 --> 00:37:29,705
You've been like this from the start.

587
00:37:29,705 --> 00:37:30,972
Ever since

588
00:37:30,972 --> 00:37:34,205
you labeled Lee Ki Beom
as a witness rather than a suspect.

589
00:37:34,205 --> 00:37:36,272
You're excessively favorable toward him.

590
00:37:36,272 --> 00:37:39,505
- It's not that.
- Then what is it?

591
00:37:39,505 --> 00:37:42,472
If Lee Ki Beom is the culprit
in the attack on you,

592
00:37:42,472 --> 00:37:44,972
there's an unexplained gap
in his movements that day.

593
00:37:44,972 --> 00:37:48,405
It really feels like two separate people
were in the same place that day.

594
00:37:48,405 --> 00:37:52,872
Ki Beom is one, and the person who kidnapped
Sun Young and attacked you is another.

595
00:37:53,938 --> 00:37:56,272
- But...
- But what?

596
00:37:59,905 --> 00:38:04,138
Lee Ki Beom was spotted
near victim Lee Joo Hee's house.

597
00:38:04,138 --> 00:38:06,738
Right after the estimated time of the crime.

598
00:38:11,205 --> 00:38:13,072
I was wrong.

599
00:38:15,738 --> 00:38:18,772
The evidence confirms
Lee Ki Beom is the killer.

600
00:38:24,505 --> 00:38:26,972
Thanks for saving Sun Young.

601
00:38:27,638 --> 00:38:31,205
I haven't told her yet
because she's still disoriented.

602
00:38:31,205 --> 00:38:32,838
I'm sorry...

603
00:38:41,005 --> 00:38:42,605
to you,

604
00:38:43,472 --> 00:38:45,772
and to Ms. Sun Young.

605
00:38:45,772 --> 00:38:47,672
I said I'm sorry.

606
00:39:38,638 --> 00:39:40,472
Sun Young, what's wrong?

607
00:39:42,538 --> 00:39:45,872
Did you have a nightmare?

608
00:39:45,872 --> 00:39:47,938
Oh, just a dream?

609
00:39:48,838 --> 00:39:50,972
Is it because you're worried about Ki Beom?

610
00:39:50,972 --> 00:39:54,438
Ji Won, something feels off.

611
00:39:54,438 --> 00:39:59,672
He left like that,
but he hasn't contacted me once.

612
00:39:59,672 --> 00:40:01,738
That's unlike Ki Beom.

613
00:40:02,972 --> 00:40:05,705
Honestly, that's been bothering me too.

614
00:40:07,705 --> 00:40:09,405
I'll check at Ki Hwan's place.

615
00:40:09,405 --> 00:40:12,638
He might have contacted home.

616
00:40:12,638 --> 00:40:14,238
Let's go together.

617
00:40:16,572 --> 00:40:19,738
Yeah, alright, let's go together.

618
00:40:23,772 --> 00:40:26,272
Well... hello?

619
00:40:26,272 --> 00:40:28,338
- Oh!
- Is Seok Man home?

620
00:40:28,338 --> 00:40:31,005
Seok Man's out right now.

621
00:40:31,005 --> 00:40:34,205
By any chance,
has my younger brother been here?

622
00:40:34,205 --> 00:40:36,938
No, he hasn't even shown his face lately.

623
00:40:36,938 --> 00:40:38,605
Tell Ki Beom to come visit.

624
00:40:38,605 --> 00:40:40,305
My daughters are looking for him.

625
00:40:40,305 --> 00:40:43,905
They're asking when the handsome guy
is coming. They're going crazy.

626
00:40:44,672 --> 00:40:46,305
Okay.

627
00:41:01,038 --> 00:41:03,105
Aren't you getting off here?

628
00:41:03,105 --> 00:41:04,338
I'm... I'm sorry.

629
00:41:04,338 --> 00:41:06,238
Oh, for heaven's sake.

630
00:41:19,138 --> 00:41:21,038
Where do you think you're going, you punk?

631
00:41:21,038 --> 00:41:23,538
Oh, you punk... seriously.

632
00:41:24,438 --> 00:41:27,172
Hey, hey!

633
00:41:28,172 --> 00:41:29,805
Get up!

634
00:41:30,761 --> 00:41:33,038
- Darn it!
- Ki Beom!

635
00:41:33,038 --> 00:41:36,205
This punk has no fear.

636
00:41:36,205 --> 00:41:38,238
Hey, go ahead first.

637
00:41:38,238 --> 00:41:40,872
How dare you run! Are you out of your mind?

638
00:41:43,177 --> 00:41:45,033
You punk.

639
00:41:47,241 --> 00:41:48,585
Darn it.

640
00:41:53,872 --> 00:41:55,772
So you know that punk, huh?

641
00:42:04,272 --> 00:42:08,873
Don't say a word about what you just saw.

642
00:42:10,905 --> 00:42:12,705
Unless you want to die.

643
00:42:44,405 --> 00:42:46,038
Hey, you punk!

644
00:42:46,038 --> 00:42:48,809
Speak, you punk!

645
00:42:48,809 --> 00:42:51,296
I said say it.

646
00:42:53,961 --> 00:42:55,432
Say it, you punk!

647
00:42:56,393 --> 00:42:58,538
Spit it out, you punk!

648
00:42:58,538 --> 00:43:01,105
You stubborn punk!

649
00:43:02,972 --> 00:43:05,805
Hey, spit it out!

650
00:43:05,805 --> 00:43:08,005
You killed them all, didn't you?

651
00:43:08,905 --> 00:43:10,772
You punk!

652
00:43:12,705 --> 00:43:17,105
This guy is seriously getting on my nerves.

653
00:43:17,105 --> 00:43:20,905
Hey, haven't I seen you somewhere?

654
00:43:22,238 --> 00:43:24,672
You punk, seriously...

655
00:43:26,905 --> 00:43:29,972
Hey, go easy on him.

656
00:43:31,305 --> 00:43:35,105
Don't worry. I didn't touch his face.

657
00:43:35,105 --> 00:43:36,438
He still won't say where the handkerchief is?

658
00:43:36,438 --> 00:43:39,172
He just keeps saying he lost it.

659
00:43:39,172 --> 00:43:41,372
We got the search warrant.

660
00:43:41,372 --> 00:43:43,005
Really?

661
00:43:46,409 --> 00:43:48,972
Oh, how touching!

662
00:43:48,972 --> 00:43:52,372
Did you come to pick me up
because I'm getting discharged?

663
00:43:52,372 --> 00:43:54,805
Sign this.

664
00:43:54,805 --> 00:43:56,405
What is this?

665
00:44:00,472 --> 00:44:02,905
A search warrant?

666
00:44:02,905 --> 00:44:05,038
I need to catch the culprit.

667
00:44:05,038 --> 00:44:06,072
As soon as possible.

668
00:44:06,072 --> 00:44:07,938
How soon?

669
00:44:07,938 --> 00:44:10,338
Before the new task force is set up.

670
00:44:10,338 --> 00:44:13,705
Before your brother gets to put everything
he's prepared into motion.

671
00:44:13,705 --> 00:44:16,772
Hey, I like that.

672
00:44:16,772 --> 00:44:19,038
I like that a lot.

673
00:44:21,305 --> 00:44:24,272
Looks like Kang Tae Joo
got it approved. Darn it.

674
00:44:24,272 --> 00:44:26,438
When we suggested it, he ignored us.

675
00:44:26,438 --> 00:44:29,172
As long as we got it, it's fine.

676
00:44:29,172 --> 00:44:30,772
What should we do?

677
00:44:32,938 --> 00:44:35,505
Alright, let's go!

678
00:44:36,438 --> 00:44:38,172
Hey!

679
00:44:40,638 --> 00:44:42,738
Speak, you punk!

680
00:44:46,638 --> 00:44:48,238
Ma'am.

681
00:44:53,438 --> 00:44:55,972
Sun Young, what brings you here?

682
00:44:55,972 --> 00:44:58,105
I came to ask if there's been
any contact from Ki Beom.

683
00:44:58,105 --> 00:45:00,438
Why do you care about that?

684
00:45:00,438 --> 00:45:02,838
Didn't you say you were done with Ki Beom?

685
00:45:02,838 --> 00:45:04,705
Ma'am, this is important.

686
00:45:04,705 --> 00:45:06,438
Where is Ki Beom now?

687
00:45:06,438 --> 00:45:08,972
In Haenam. He's at a friend's place.

688
00:45:08,972 --> 00:45:10,738
Really? Are you sure?

689
00:45:10,738 --> 00:45:13,538
He called and said he was doing fine.

690
00:45:13,538 --> 00:45:15,372
Isn't that right?

691
00:45:16,838 --> 00:45:19,605
Jeong Sook,
did you really get a call from him?

692
00:45:20,738 --> 00:45:22,872
Well, actually...

693
00:45:26,005 --> 00:45:29,305
Wow, the weather's really rough today.

694
00:45:29,305 --> 00:45:30,972
Alright, line up.

695
00:45:32,872 --> 00:45:35,472
If you find anything suspicious
during the search,

696
00:45:35,472 --> 00:45:37,472
seize it immediately. Got it?

697
00:45:37,472 --> 00:45:39,272
- Yes, sir!
- Okay.

698
00:45:39,272 --> 00:45:41,372
Excuse me, what's going on here?

699
00:45:41,372 --> 00:45:44,505
What? Is that really true?

700
00:45:44,505 --> 00:45:48,972
So you haven't heard
from Ki Beom at all? Not even once?

701
00:45:48,972 --> 00:45:51,805
Why are you only saying this now?

702
00:45:51,805 --> 00:45:55,572
Ki Hwan told me not to tell you,
afraid it would only worry you.

703
00:45:56,572 --> 00:45:59,472
- Let's go inside.
- What are you doing right now?

704
00:45:59,472 --> 00:46:02,729
Darn it. An insect.

705
00:46:05,672 --> 00:46:07,405
Honey!

706
00:46:07,405 --> 00:46:08,405
Ki Hwan!

707
00:46:08,405 --> 00:46:10,238
Mr. Jang, what are you doing?

708
00:46:10,238 --> 00:46:11,738
Ms. Seo, you're here too.

709
00:46:11,738 --> 00:46:12,838
Are you Lee Ki Beom's mother?

710
00:46:12,838 --> 00:46:16,672
- Yes.
- This is a search warrant for Lee Ki Beom.

711
00:46:16,672 --> 00:46:18,638
We ask for your cooperation.

712
00:46:18,638 --> 00:46:20,705
- Search everything thoroughly! Every corner!
- Yes, sir!

713
00:46:20,705 --> 00:46:22,605
No, wait...

714
00:46:22,605 --> 00:46:25,417
Oh, my. Why are you doing this?

715
00:46:29,225 --> 00:46:32,272
- Mother.
- Why are you doing this?

716
00:46:32,272 --> 00:46:35,572
- Search it thoroughly!
- What are you doing?

717
00:46:35,572 --> 00:46:38,805
What are we going to do?

718
00:46:38,805 --> 00:46:41,438
Where should we start?

719
00:46:41,438 --> 00:46:43,005
[Kangseng Bookstore]

720
00:46:43,005 --> 00:46:45,672
Hey, don't miss a single spot.
Search everything!

721
00:46:45,672 --> 00:46:47,305
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

722
00:46:51,683 --> 00:46:53,763
[Please claim your lost items]

723
00:47:00,838 --> 00:47:02,438
[Capital]

724
00:47:02,438 --> 00:47:05,838
So he's even been acting
like a darn communist...

725
00:47:05,838 --> 00:47:06,972
Wait...

726
00:47:06,972 --> 00:47:09,705
Stop right there, you punk!

727
00:47:15,205 --> 00:47:17,938
Got you, you little rat!

728
00:47:17,938 --> 00:47:21,891
[Please claim your lost items]

729
00:47:30,105 --> 00:47:32,205
Just leave it to other detectives.

730
00:47:32,205 --> 00:47:34,872
You don't have to personally get involved.

731
00:47:35,945 --> 00:47:37,938
Hey, you punk!

732
00:47:40,672 --> 00:47:42,305
Jeez, your stubbornness...

733
00:47:42,305 --> 00:47:43,838
Shouldn't you at least tell us
why you're doing this?

734
00:47:43,838 --> 00:47:46,472
Move aside, unless you want to
be hauled in for obstructing justice.

735
00:47:46,472 --> 00:47:48,838
What exactly did my brother do wrong?

736
00:47:48,838 --> 00:47:51,372
What's with all the questions?

737
00:47:51,372 --> 00:47:55,138
Your brother Lee Ki Beom
is a serial murder suspect.

738
00:47:55,805 --> 00:47:58,605
What did you just say?

739
00:47:58,605 --> 00:48:00,238
Serial murder?

740
00:48:00,238 --> 00:48:04,272
That's ridiculous. Even a passing dog
would laugh at that!

741
00:48:04,905 --> 00:48:06,972
- Tae Joo!
- Detective Kang, what took you so long?

742
00:48:06,972 --> 00:48:08,738
- Tae Joo!
- Prosecutor Cha!

743
00:48:08,738 --> 00:48:11,305
Tae Joo, perfect timing!

744
00:48:11,305 --> 00:48:13,605
These punks are completely delusional.

745
00:48:13,605 --> 00:48:17,405
They're calling our Ki Beom a serial killer.

746
00:48:17,405 --> 00:48:21,838
My boy couldn't even hurt a fly.
How could he kill anyone?

747
00:48:21,838 --> 00:48:25,038
Tae Joo, get through to these idiots.

748
00:48:25,038 --> 00:48:27,805
First, calm the mother down.

749
00:48:29,372 --> 00:48:32,138
Ki Beom really is a serial murder suspect.

750
00:48:32,138 --> 00:48:34,205
He is currently on the run.

751
00:48:34,205 --> 00:48:36,605
Have you had any contact with him?

752
00:48:36,605 --> 00:48:39,038
We must find Ki Beom, ma'am.

753
00:48:41,838 --> 00:48:44,838
You think Ki Beom's a suspect too?

754
00:48:46,672 --> 00:48:49,072
Hey, answer me!

755
00:48:49,072 --> 00:48:53,138
I said, do you doubt him too?

756
00:48:54,472 --> 00:48:56,105
- Yes.
- What?

757
00:49:01,838 --> 00:49:04,538
We have grounds for suspicion,
so we have to investigate.

758
00:49:04,538 --> 00:49:07,072
If Ki Beom's been framed, I'll prove it.

759
00:49:07,072 --> 00:49:10,138
And if he's the real culprit,
I'll make sure he's caught.

760
00:49:10,138 --> 00:49:12,672
So if you trust Ki Beom,

761
00:49:12,672 --> 00:49:15,238
trust me and cooperate
with the investigation.

762
00:49:16,172 --> 00:49:18,205
This is the suspect's room.
Start the search here.

763
00:49:18,205 --> 00:49:19,205
You...

764
00:49:19,205 --> 00:49:20,505
You little punk, I'll...

765
00:49:20,505 --> 00:49:22,472
Mother, Mother!

766
00:49:22,472 --> 00:49:23,505
- Let go!
- Please calm down.

767
00:49:23,505 --> 00:49:26,272
Won't you let go? Let go of me!

768
00:49:29,438 --> 00:49:31,438
This is all your fault!

769
00:49:31,438 --> 00:49:34,738
If you, as the eldest,
had chosen your friends wisely,

770
00:49:34,738 --> 00:49:36,905
would this have happened?

771
00:49:36,905 --> 00:49:37,905
Please stop, ma'am.

772
00:49:37,905 --> 00:49:40,405
Don't touch me.

773
00:49:40,405 --> 00:49:44,438
I was the one who fed you and your sister

774
00:49:44,438 --> 00:49:47,305
when your own mother didn't!

775
00:49:47,305 --> 00:49:49,005
And now you, of all people...

776
00:49:49,005 --> 00:49:52,538
are trying to destroy my son?

777
00:49:53,372 --> 00:49:56,872
- Mother!
- Mother!

778
00:49:56,872 --> 00:49:58,905
- Mother!
- Mother!

779
00:49:58,905 --> 00:50:00,172
Mother, are you okay?

780
00:50:00,172 --> 00:50:01,338
Mother!

781
00:50:01,338 --> 00:50:03,372
Take your hand off me.

782
00:50:33,305 --> 00:50:34,905
Sun Young, you...

783
00:50:36,005 --> 00:50:37,838
Don't tell me it's his...

784
00:50:39,205 --> 00:50:41,193
It's Ki Beom's child.

785
00:50:41,193 --> 00:50:42,738
Jeez.

786
00:50:42,738 --> 00:50:43,972
You... seriously?

787
00:50:43,972 --> 00:50:45,972
Have you lost your mind?

788
00:50:45,972 --> 00:50:47,672
That guy is a serial killer!

789
00:50:47,672 --> 00:50:48,672
How could you carry his child?

790
00:50:48,672 --> 00:50:50,338
Don't say that!

791
00:50:50,338 --> 00:50:52,138
Ki Beom's not a serial killer.

792
00:50:52,138 --> 00:50:53,738
I remembered what happened that day.

793
00:50:53,738 --> 00:50:57,272
I clearly remember the person
who dragged me away from behind.

794
00:50:57,272 --> 00:51:00,472
- It wasn't Ki Beom.
- Don't talk nonsense!

795
00:51:00,472 --> 00:51:02,938
There weren't any streetlights
in those fields where you were taken!

796
00:51:02,938 --> 00:51:04,605
You couldn't see anything!

797
00:51:04,605 --> 00:51:08,438
He was limping, like he was injured.
I swear it's true!

798
00:51:08,438 --> 00:51:10,038
Enough!

799
00:51:13,305 --> 00:51:15,538
Even if you're telling the truth,
I can't believe you.

800
00:51:15,538 --> 00:51:19,438
You'd even twist your own memories
to protect Ki Beom.

801
00:51:21,538 --> 00:51:23,505
- Tae Joo.
- Sun Young.

802
00:51:23,505 --> 00:51:24,772
Go wait in my car.

803
00:51:24,772 --> 00:51:26,138
Ji Won, but...

804
00:51:26,138 --> 00:51:29,321
Nothing you say will change anything.
Don't waste your energy. Just go.

805
00:51:29,321 --> 00:51:30,761
Go on ahead.

806
00:51:31,705 --> 00:51:33,705
Go.

807
00:51:33,705 --> 00:51:35,338
Go on ahead.

808
00:51:40,005 --> 00:51:42,305
Are you seriously not going to
investigate this properly?

809
00:51:44,405 --> 00:51:48,138
I'm doing this now because I'm trying
to investigate properly.

810
00:51:48,138 --> 00:51:51,072
If I hadn't trusted that punk and hesitated,

811
00:51:51,072 --> 00:51:52,505
it never would've come to this.

812
00:51:52,505 --> 00:51:54,205
Give me a break.

813
00:51:54,205 --> 00:51:56,405
Hey, don't fool yourself.

814
00:51:56,405 --> 00:51:59,005
You're not some warm-hearted guy.

815
00:51:59,005 --> 00:52:02,172
You acted that way simply
because there wasn't enough evidence.

816
00:52:02,172 --> 00:52:05,538
Because things didn't add up.
There were gaps you couldn't explain.

817
00:52:05,538 --> 00:52:09,305
That's just who you are, Kang Tae Joo!

818
00:52:21,705 --> 00:52:23,625
Jeez.

819
00:52:34,172 --> 00:52:36,405
- Huh?
- What is that?

820
00:52:36,405 --> 00:52:38,005
This...

821
00:52:39,938 --> 00:52:41,538
This punk.

822
00:52:42,605 --> 00:52:44,238
Look at this.

823
00:52:47,905 --> 00:52:49,505
Detective Kang!

824
00:52:50,438 --> 00:52:53,938
I knew you had some connection
with Lee Ki Beom,

825
00:52:53,938 --> 00:52:56,738
but I didn't realize you were this close.

826
00:53:01,481 --> 00:53:03,433
[Wedding Reception]

827
00:53:06,638 --> 00:53:08,638
Hey, it's been a while.

828
00:53:08,638 --> 00:53:10,605
You're late, Tae Joo.

829
00:53:10,605 --> 00:53:12,872
I had something to deal with,
so I left Seoul late.

830
00:53:12,872 --> 00:53:13,872
Where is the groom?

831
00:53:13,872 --> 00:53:15,072
He went to the restroom.

832
00:53:15,072 --> 00:53:16,372
I think he's got an upset stomach.

833
00:53:16,372 --> 00:53:18,438
He must've eaten everything they gave him.

834
00:53:18,438 --> 00:53:19,438
No wonder.

835
00:53:19,438 --> 00:53:21,105
- Hello!
- Hello!

836
00:53:21,105 --> 00:53:23,005
It's been a while.

837
00:53:23,005 --> 00:53:26,938
Everyone else is getting married.
When are you going to?

838
00:53:26,938 --> 00:53:28,638
Do you at least have a girlfriend?

839
00:53:28,638 --> 00:53:31,005
- Well, that's...
- Tae Joo!

840
00:53:31,005 --> 00:53:32,438
Why are you so late?

841
00:53:32,438 --> 00:53:34,738
The wedding's already over.

842
00:53:34,738 --> 00:53:37,238
I came all this way,
so you should at least thank me.

843
00:53:37,238 --> 00:53:38,905
You punk...

844
00:53:38,905 --> 00:53:40,038
Here, this is for the wedding.

845
00:53:40,038 --> 00:53:41,838
Thank you!

846
00:53:41,838 --> 00:53:44,972
Tae Joo, let's take a picture together.
We should at least have one.

847
00:53:44,972 --> 00:53:46,738
I'm dressed like this.
How am I supposed to take a picture?

848
00:53:46,738 --> 00:53:47,905
I'll take a picture of you two.

849
00:53:47,905 --> 00:53:49,938
Ki Beom, you should take one with us.

850
00:53:49,938 --> 00:53:51,972
Yong Tae, take a picture of us here.

851
00:53:51,972 --> 00:53:53,905
Alright.

852
00:53:53,905 --> 00:53:55,505
Just one shot, please.

853
00:54:01,438 --> 00:54:03,005
Okay, look here.

854
00:54:03,005 --> 00:54:05,872
One, two, three!

855
00:54:11,305 --> 00:54:14,638
<i>December 13, 1987.</i>

856
00:54:16,172 --> 00:54:20,472
If you were this close, shouldn't you
have recused yourself from the investigation?

857
00:54:22,838 --> 00:54:24,538
Hey, Kang Tae Joo!

858
00:54:26,538 --> 00:54:28,905
That punk...

859
00:54:28,905 --> 00:54:30,972
He's running now that it's not in his favor.

860
00:54:44,705 --> 00:54:46,838
Choi In Sook, Choi In Sook...

861
00:54:52,538 --> 00:54:57,038
[Choi In Sook's Records]
Choi In Sook, missing on December 13, 1987.

862
00:54:57,038 --> 00:55:01,005
Estimated time of the crime, 8:30 PM.

863
00:55:11,472 --> 00:55:13,838
Ki Beom was with me at that time.

864
00:55:15,338 --> 00:55:17,472
How did this happen?

865
00:55:17,472 --> 00:55:20,205
Who would've thought it would turn up there?

866
00:55:20,205 --> 00:55:21,838
- Right.
- Oh, Kang Tae Joo!

867
00:55:21,838 --> 00:55:23,172
You are already here?

868
00:55:23,172 --> 00:55:26,372
Sir, we found evidence
that Lee Ki Beom is the culprit.

869
00:55:26,372 --> 00:55:27,605
What?

870
00:55:27,605 --> 00:55:29,205
Here.

871
00:55:32,605 --> 00:55:34,205
What is this?

872
00:55:35,872 --> 00:55:38,772
[Please claim your lost items]

873
00:55:48,405 --> 00:55:50,005
Inside this,

874
00:55:50,838 --> 00:55:52,438
[Park Ae Sook]
we found this.

875
00:55:58,738 --> 00:56:00,305
This belongs to Park Ae Sook's?

876
00:56:00,305 --> 00:56:01,972
Yes.

877
00:56:01,972 --> 00:56:04,972
We just came back after confirming it
directly with Park Ae Sook.

878
00:56:04,972 --> 00:56:07,572
She said she lost it on the day of the crime.

879
00:56:07,572 --> 00:56:10,472
[Resident Registration Card, Park Ae Sook]

880
00:56:11,438 --> 00:56:14,638
Where could the prosecutor be?

881
00:56:14,638 --> 00:56:17,705
[Capital 1-1, Capital 1-2]
Maybe at the office?

882
00:56:17,705 --> 00:56:20,405
Got him, got him!

883
00:56:20,405 --> 00:56:21,705
I'll go report and come back.

884
00:56:21,705 --> 00:56:23,338
Yes, sir.

885
00:56:30,372 --> 00:56:33,072
<i>Park Ae Sook's handbag
found in the bookstore.</i>

886
00:56:33,072 --> 00:56:36,372
<i>That's evidence that Ki Beom is the culprit.</i>

887
00:56:36,372 --> 00:56:40,705
<i>But the photo found at the house
proves Ki Beom has an alibi.</i>

888
00:56:40,705 --> 00:56:44,138
<i>Two pieces of evidence are telling
completely opposite truths.</i>

889
00:56:45,305 --> 00:56:47,338
<i>What is this?</i>

890
00:56:47,338 --> 00:56:49,772
<i>What am I missing here?</i>

891
00:56:51,738 --> 00:56:54,005
Tae Joo!

892
00:56:55,272 --> 00:56:57,338
What did you mean earlier?

893
00:56:57,338 --> 00:57:00,438
Why did you say our Ki Beom is a murderer?

894
00:57:00,438 --> 00:57:02,072
Ki Hwan, let's talk later.

895
00:57:02,072 --> 00:57:03,705
Hey!

896
00:57:05,472 --> 00:57:08,405
When did you start suspecting Ki Beom?

897
00:57:09,572 --> 00:57:11,505
Don't tell me it was from
when you came to my house?

898
00:57:11,505 --> 00:57:14,005
The settlement was just an excuse,

899
00:57:14,005 --> 00:57:16,072
and you came to find our Ki Beom?

900
00:57:16,072 --> 00:57:17,738
Is that it?

901
00:57:19,838 --> 00:57:20,972
Answer me, you punk!

902
00:57:20,972 --> 00:57:22,938
How could I not suspect him?

903
00:57:23,572 --> 00:57:25,138
What?

904
00:57:25,138 --> 00:57:27,905
A victim's belonging
was found at the bookstore,

905
00:57:27,905 --> 00:57:31,405
and the last places victims Yu Jeong Rin
and Kim Min Ji visited were your bookstore.

906
00:57:31,405 --> 00:57:33,805
And the suspect was wearing
Ki Beom's handkerchief!

907
00:57:34,872 --> 00:57:37,772
So how could I not suspect Ki Beom?

908
00:57:37,772 --> 00:57:41,038
What came out of the bookstore?

909
00:57:43,038 --> 00:57:45,505
Ki Hwan, this is...

910
00:57:45,505 --> 00:57:48,672
It doesn't make sense
unless Ki Beom is the real culprit.

911
00:57:48,672 --> 00:57:50,738
If not Ki Beom, then who...

912
00:57:55,238 --> 00:58:00,872
<i>Someone besides Ki Beom who can enter
both the bookstore and the house.</i>

913
00:58:02,438 --> 00:58:04,072
<i>There is...</i>

914
00:58:05,705 --> 00:58:07,672
<i>another suspect.</i>

915
00:58:19,572 --> 00:58:23,005
Mr. Lee Yong Woo, have you been well?

916
00:58:23,772 --> 00:58:25,638
Where is he?

917
00:58:25,638 --> 00:58:28,838
Professor Kang Tae Joo
has returned to his main job.

918
00:58:28,838 --> 00:58:32,105
He needs to finish his research paper too.

919
00:58:32,105 --> 00:58:37,272
Are you saying that meeting me
is less important than his paper?

920
00:58:37,272 --> 00:58:39,338
It's not like that.

921
00:58:44,838 --> 00:58:48,105
Lee Yong Woo has clammed up again.

922
00:58:48,838 --> 00:58:52,038
He's gone back to how he was
when we first met.

923
00:58:52,705 --> 00:58:56,705
He's not only hostile,
but he's also being really spiteful.

924
00:58:57,505 --> 00:59:01,405
Why did you quit, anyway?

925
00:59:01,405 --> 00:59:04,605
You really built a good rapport
with Lee Yong Woo.

926
00:59:04,605 --> 00:59:07,305
Now, that kind of thing
should be handled by active-duty officers.

927
00:59:07,305 --> 00:59:10,272
Don't think about using an old man like me.

928
00:59:10,272 --> 00:59:12,872
Please tell me how to do it, sir.

929
00:59:12,872 --> 00:59:15,805
How to make Lee Yong Woo talk?

930
00:59:19,538 --> 00:59:23,372
Lee Yong Woo has already made up his mind.

931
00:59:23,372 --> 00:59:25,605
He's decided to tell the truth.

932
00:59:26,305 --> 00:59:28,638
So it won't be difficult.

933
00:59:33,572 --> 00:59:35,905
Oh, and...

934
00:59:35,905 --> 00:59:39,372
Lee Yong Woo asked me
to pass this to you, sir.

935
00:59:40,772 --> 00:59:43,505
He said it was a gift or something.

936
00:59:43,505 --> 00:59:45,138
A gift?

937
00:59:46,438 --> 00:59:50,438
[Murder: 12+2, Rape: 19, Attempted: 15]

938
00:59:52,638 --> 00:59:54,138
What is this?

939
00:59:54,138 --> 00:59:55,438
What are these numbers?

940
00:59:55,438 --> 00:59:57,572
[Murder: 12+2, Rape: 19, Attempted: 15]

941
01:00:01,705 --> 01:00:03,372
The truth.

942
01:00:36,505 --> 01:00:39,538
The suspect is a Mr. Lee
residing in Kangseng...

943
01:00:39,538 --> 01:00:41,638
Lee Ki Beom has just
made his first confession.

944
01:00:41,638 --> 01:00:43,605
Ki Beom, is it really you?

945
01:00:43,605 --> 01:00:44,672
Answer me!

946
01:00:44,672 --> 01:00:45,772
Was it really you?

947
01:00:45,772 --> 01:00:47,772
So that's why you tried
to kill Sun Young too?

948
01:00:47,772 --> 01:00:50,205
But she's not my family.

949
01:00:52,205 --> 01:00:55,772
Are you the real culprit
in the serial murder case?

950
01:00:55,772 --> 01:00:57,272
Is this actually Lee Ki Beom's statement?

951
01:00:57,272 --> 01:00:58,505
It's all just things we already know.

952
01:00:58,505 --> 01:00:59,705
And some of it is completely wrong.

953
01:00:59,705 --> 01:01:01,005
Unlawful confinement and assault!

954
01:01:01,005 --> 01:01:03,605
If Prosecutor Cha finds out
everything you've done...

